1
00:02:40,319 --> 00:02:40,960
Remember.

2
00:02:41,879 --> 00:02:42,719
Take them alive.

3
00:02:42,960 --> 00:02:44,000
Unless absolutely necessary,

4
00:02:44,360 --> 00:02:45,280
do not open fire.

5
00:02:45,680 --> 00:02:46,280
Understood?

6
00:02:47,159 --> 00:02:47,680
Da Liu.

7
00:02:48,199 --> 00:02:49,120
Take your men and secure the main gate.

8
00:02:49,919 --> 00:02:51,479
Jiang Han, upstairs with me.

9
00:02:51,599 --> 00:02:51,960
Yes, sir.

10
00:02:51,960 --> 00:02:52,479
Move out.

11
00:03:43,280 --> 00:03:44,039
Ma Shijiang!

12
00:03:46,080 --> 00:03:47,840
Ma Shijiang, stop right there!

13
00:03:52,560 --> 00:03:53,319
Da Liu, Da Liu!

14
00:03:53,759 --> 00:03:54,800
The suspect ran to the backyard!

15
00:03:54,800 --> 00:03:55,639
Cut him off, quick!

16
00:03:56,080 --> 00:03:57,599
Got it. You two, head to the back!

17
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:01,520
Jiang Han!

18
00:04:01,960 --> 00:04:02,680
Block him off downstairs!

19
00:04:17,839 --> 00:04:18,480
Freeze!

20
00:04:20,160 --> 00:04:21,720
Ma Shijiang, I said freeze!

21
00:04:31,160 --> 00:04:31,839
Ma Shijiang!

22
00:04:33,199 --> 00:04:34,360
This is your final warning!

23
00:04:35,319 --> 00:04:36,600
Keep running and I'll shoot!

24
00:04:45,800 --> 00:04:47,000
Go ahead, shoot if you dare!

25
00:04:48,839 --> 00:04:49,759
If I die,

26
00:04:50,360 --> 00:04:51,480
the truth dies with me.

27
00:04:52,120 --> 00:04:53,279
You cops

28
00:04:53,759 --> 00:04:55,240
will be fools for the rest of your lives.

29
00:04:56,680 --> 00:04:58,000
I didn't kill that girl.

30
00:04:59,279 --> 00:05:00,519
She was hit by a car.

31
00:05:01,560 --> 00:05:03,040
I was just looking for some fun.

32
00:05:05,040 --> 00:05:06,040
Just my bad luck.

33
00:05:07,600 --> 00:05:09,480
And I didn't rape your sister, Ruolan, either.

34
00:05:10,959 --> 00:05:11,800
Although

35
00:05:13,079 --> 00:05:14,480
I've dreamed of sleeping with her.

36
00:05:26,399 --> 00:05:27,199
Shoot!

37
00:05:29,240 --> 00:05:30,560
Worst case, we die together.

38
00:05:34,480 --> 00:05:35,240
That night,

39
00:05:36,800 --> 00:05:38,279
that bastard knocked me out cold.

40
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:42,360
I didn't rape Ruolan.

41
00:05:43,439 --> 00:05:45,160
Come on, shoot if you've got the guts!

42
00:05:46,959 --> 00:05:48,360
Worst case, we both go to hell together.

43
00:06:52,160 --> 00:06:53,720
Brother.

44
00:07:10,839 --> 00:07:12,199
Brother.

45
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:38,000
Kaiyang.

46
00:08:40,519 --> 00:08:41,679
Pulling a long face again.

47
00:08:42,759 --> 00:08:43,840
Your face is already long enough,

48
00:08:44,919 --> 00:08:46,159
almost like a mill donkey's.

49
00:08:47,679 --> 00:08:49,000
People who smile

50
00:08:49,440 --> 00:08:50,440
live longer.

51
00:08:51,480 --> 00:08:52,240
Look at me.

52
00:09:02,919 --> 00:09:03,600
Kaiyang,

53
00:09:04,960 --> 00:09:06,080
let me take this one.

54
00:09:12,919 --> 00:09:14,399
Keep an eye on my silly apprentice for me.

55
00:09:14,759 --> 00:09:15,480
Don't worry.

56
00:09:16,159 --> 00:09:17,120
Even if I go down,

57
00:09:18,399 --> 00:09:19,360
he'll be fine.

58
00:09:19,480 --> 00:09:20,360
Talking nonsense again.

59
00:09:21,200 --> 00:09:21,879
One more word of that nonsense,

60
00:09:21,879 --> 00:09:22,759
and I'll rip your mouth off.

61
00:09:23,679 --> 00:09:24,600
I told you,

62
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:25,840
I told you to stop talking nonsense.

63
00:09:28,039 --> 00:09:29,039
Why didn't you listen?

64
00:09:52,320 --> 00:09:52,960
Okay.

65
00:09:54,279 --> 00:09:55,080
Got it.

66
00:10:04,399 --> 00:10:06,679
Boss, you're finally awake.

67
00:10:06,919 --> 00:10:08,080
You scared me to death.

68
00:10:11,320 --> 00:10:12,240
Where's Captain Zhao?

69
00:10:19,200 --> 00:10:20,399
I'm asking you, where's Captain Zhao?

70
00:10:28,159 --> 00:10:28,879
Captain Zhao...

71
00:10:33,080 --> 00:10:34,200
Captain Zhao died in the line of duty.

72
00:10:39,039 --> 00:10:39,600
Right.

73
00:10:40,440 --> 00:10:41,320
Right, he's gone.

74
00:10:44,120 --> 00:10:44,919
Boss.

75
00:10:46,159 --> 00:10:47,080
It's my fault.

76
00:10:47,960 --> 00:10:49,200
I failed to protect Captain Zhao.

77
00:10:49,879 --> 00:10:51,240
Hit me, curse me, do whatever.

78
00:10:51,399 --> 00:10:52,440
I'm useless.

79
00:10:52,679 --> 00:10:53,799
What happened that day?

80
00:10:55,639 --> 00:10:56,600
How did Captain Zhao die?

81
00:10:58,080 --> 00:10:58,919
Boss.

82
00:11:00,360 --> 00:11:01,679
You already asked me that.

83
00:11:01,679 --> 00:11:02,720
Tell me again.

84
00:11:07,919 --> 00:11:08,440
That day...

85
00:11:14,559 --> 00:11:16,120
Captain Zhao... Captain Zhao...

86
00:11:29,399 --> 00:11:30,679
Captain Zhao was at the police academy.

87
00:11:31,440 --> 00:11:32,519
He was an instructor.

88
00:11:33,240 --> 00:11:34,360
He had serious combat skills.

89
00:11:35,600 --> 00:11:37,440
You think Ma Shijiang could kill him?

90
00:11:44,399 --> 00:11:45,200
What about Da Liu?

91
00:11:47,159 --> 00:11:48,519
He just handed in his resignation.

92
00:11:49,440 --> 00:11:50,399
He's left the force.

93
00:11:53,799 --> 00:11:54,559
Resigned?

94
00:11:56,840 --> 00:11:57,679
When?

95
00:11:59,039 --> 00:11:59,960
Last night.

96
00:12:00,639 --> 00:12:01,320
Boss.

97
00:12:02,240 --> 00:12:03,720
You've been asleep for a whole day and night.

98
00:12:07,279 --> 00:12:08,240
Hey, Boss.

99
00:12:09,080 --> 00:12:09,879
What are you doing?

100
00:12:10,039 --> 00:12:11,639
Chief Xing ordered you to get some proper rest.

101
00:12:12,159 --> 00:12:13,240
Any more sleep and I'll be dead.

102
00:12:14,600 --> 00:12:15,240
Where's Ruolan?

103
00:12:15,720 --> 00:12:16,360
Where is she?

104
00:12:16,799 --> 00:12:17,960
Lin Xue just called.

105
00:12:18,320 --> 00:12:19,639
She said Ruolan insisted on going back to check.

106
00:12:19,879 --> 00:12:20,960
So she took her back.

107
00:12:22,720 --> 00:12:23,440
Don't worry.

108
00:12:24,799 --> 00:12:25,799
No matter what,

109
00:12:27,919 --> 00:12:29,440
I'll treat Ruolan like my own sister.

110
00:12:36,440 --> 00:12:37,120
Brother.

111
00:12:41,200 --> 00:12:42,120
I'm leaving Ruolan in your hands.

112
00:12:43,440 --> 00:12:44,240
Oh no.

113
00:12:45,559 --> 00:12:46,279
Boss.

114
00:13:09,720 --> 00:13:10,440
Brother.

115
00:13:18,200 --> 00:13:18,879
Brother.

116
00:13:21,480 --> 00:13:22,120
Ruolan.

117
00:13:31,519 --> 00:13:32,200
Brother.

118
00:13:39,279 --> 00:13:39,919
Brother.

119
00:13:43,320 --> 00:13:44,080
Brother.

120
00:13:44,799 --> 00:13:45,480
Brother.

121
00:14:07,919 --> 00:14:08,639
Brother.

122
00:14:13,840 --> 00:14:14,519
Brother.

123
00:14:15,440 --> 00:14:18,879
You promised to take care of me forever.

124
00:14:20,000 --> 00:14:23,799
Why did you leave me all alone?

125
00:14:38,399 --> 00:14:39,480
Ruolan, open the door!

126
00:14:39,480 --> 00:14:40,320
It's me, Ming Liang.

127
00:14:42,840 --> 00:14:44,000
Ruolan, open the door!

128
00:14:45,320 --> 00:14:47,000
Brother Li, you came just in time.

129
00:14:47,519 --> 00:14:48,320
I've been knocking for ages,

130
00:14:48,320 --> 00:14:49,000
but Ruolan won't answer.

131
00:14:49,000 --> 00:14:49,919
Do you think something happened?

132
00:15:00,360 --> 00:15:01,399
Ruolan! Ruolan!

133
00:15:03,080 --> 00:15:03,600
Ruolan!

134
00:15:07,600 --> 00:15:08,159
So much blood!

135
00:15:08,159 --> 00:15:09,039
Call an ambulance!

136
00:15:09,039 --> 00:15:09,639
Right away!

137
00:15:10,039 --> 00:15:10,559
Ruolan.

138
00:15:11,399 --> 00:15:12,039
Ruolan.

139
00:15:22,519 --> 00:15:23,240
Boss.

140
00:15:24,200 --> 00:15:24,879
Boss.

141
00:15:26,799 --> 00:15:27,919
Can you say something?

142
00:15:28,679 --> 00:15:30,000
What happened to Ruolan really isn't your fault.

143
00:15:31,200 --> 00:15:32,440
Have you ever seen fallen leaves?

144
00:15:33,240 --> 00:15:34,080
Fallen leaves?

145
00:15:34,879 --> 00:15:36,000
Fallen leaves in summer.

146
00:15:37,960 --> 00:15:39,399
I've never really noticed.

147
00:15:40,240 --> 00:15:41,039
Look.

148
00:15:46,480 --> 00:15:47,279
This big tree

149
00:15:47,279 --> 00:15:48,879
is like the land we live on,

150
00:15:49,840 --> 00:15:51,000
like a mother.

151
00:15:53,279 --> 00:15:54,679
In this scorching summer,

152
00:15:55,320 --> 00:15:57,679
the leaves should be at their greenest.

153
00:15:57,960 --> 00:15:59,440
But just because of a bit of wind and rain,

154
00:16:01,480 --> 00:16:02,879
some leaves have fallen,

155
00:16:05,039 --> 00:16:06,600
drifting into forgotten corners.

156
00:16:06,600 --> 00:16:07,399
Withering.

157
00:16:08,279 --> 00:16:09,000
Wilting.

158
00:16:10,240 --> 00:16:11,320
Losing their lives.

159
00:16:16,519 --> 00:16:18,039
Do you pity the fallen leaves?

160
00:16:18,720 --> 00:16:20,120
Or blame the storm for being too harsh?

161
00:16:21,919 --> 00:16:22,840
Tell me,

162
00:16:25,159 --> 00:16:26,960
did the leaves abandon the tree?

163
00:16:29,200 --> 00:16:30,840
Or did the tree abandon the leaves?

164
00:16:35,799 --> 00:16:36,840
Perhaps...

165
00:16:39,120 --> 00:16:40,879
Perhaps they abandoned each other.
